data.title: Marriage of the Prince of Baden, Napoleon Bonaparte (Emperor Napoleon I), France, 1806
data.meta_description: Medal Marriage of the Prince of Baden, Issued by France, 1806 Artist: Bertrand Andrieu Minted by Paris Mint
data.text:
Summary

Medal Marriage of the Prince of Baden, Issued by France, 1806

Artist: Bertrand Andrieu

Minted by Paris Mint

Obverse Description

Laureate head right; around NAPOLEON EMP ET ROI.; on head truncation in small letters, ANDRIEU F; below, DENON DIRT.

Reverse Description

The Prince and Princess clasping hands and about to kiss; above the star of Napoleon, N within rays; at left, STEPHANIE NAPOLEON; at right, C. F. LOUIS DE BADE; in exergue, ALLIANCE MDCCCVI.; around rim in small lettering, ANDRIEU F. DENON DT.

Edge Description

Plain

Significance
